Step 1: Identify the relevant amounts from the cash flow statement.  
  • Net Profit = 1,167,783.63  
  • Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -1,368,775.90  

Step 2: Calculate the Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio using the formula:  

  Ratio = (Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities) ÷ (Net Profit)  

Step 3: Insert the values:  

  Ratio = -1,368,775.90 ÷ 1,167,783.63 ≈ -1.1723  

Step 4: Rounding to two decimal places gives -1.17.

Thus, the Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio is -1.17.
